Subject: RE: [VB] Ronnie and POR-15 advice

> What is wrong with using POR-15 as an undercoating
> underneath the bus, and then using the interior and painting over it while
> still tacky?


Just to clarify here, the way the people at POR15 explained it to me, you
should PRIMER over POR15 while it is still tacky.  But if you are PAINTING
directly over it rather than priming, you should wait until it's fully
dried.

